Sensory investigation of oils was performed using quantitative descriptive analysis. For this purpose a group of ten semi-trained panelists as of the academic personnel of Department of Food Hygiene and Quality Control of the Urmia University, Iran (4 women and 6 men, ages 23–55 yr) were recruited. Butter samples in terms of texture, color, flavor and odor and overall acceptability were determined using five point hedonic level. Sensory panel members were needed so as to score the samples from 1 to 5. (1 = Very bad; 2 = bad; 3 = good; 4 = very good; 5 = excellent) (
 Dimić et al., 2012; 
 Janiaski et al., 2016).
